# [MS-PST] §3.8 — Sample Heap-on-Node (HN)
# Source: https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/openspecs/office_file_formats/ms-pst/8773374f-8495-44fe-9614-6c4f60418489
#
# HN block IB (in the source PST) = 0x0000000000004800
# HN body size = 0x102 = 258 bytes:
#   bytes 0..0xEB    HN heap content (HNHDR + 8 user allocations)
#   bytes 0xEC..0x101 HNPAGEMAP (cAlloc=8, cFree=0, rgibAlloc[9])
#
# HNHDR (12 bytes at offset 0):
#   ibHnpm        = 0x00EC   (HNPAGEMAP starts at heap offset 0xEC)
#   bSig          = 0xEC     (kHnSignature)
#   bClientSig    = 0xBC     (bTypePC — heap belongs to a PropertyContext)
#   hidUserRoot   = 0x00000020   (PC's metadata at HID 0x20 = first allocation)
#   rgbFillLevel  = {0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0}  (all unused for first HN block)
#
# HNPAGEMAP rgibAlloc[] (offsets 0..7 are allocation starts; offset 8 is the
# next-allocation sentinel):
#   0x000C, 0x0014, 0x006C, 0x007C, 0x008C, 0x00A4, 0x00BC, 0x00D4, 0x00EC
#
# IMPORTANT: This dump shows only the HN STRUCTURED BODY. The spec page does
# NOT include the BLOCKTRAILER, so there is no stored cb / wSig / dwCRC / bid
# to compare against. Round-trip tests for §3.8 must compare structured
# bytes only.
